HEADWORD: Bridestake
<hw>Bride"stake`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stake or post
set in the ground, for guests at a wedding to dance round.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Divide the broad bridecake⟦br⟧
Round about the <qex>bridestake</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

